$ Shell command: bc
@ bc

An arbitrary precision calculator language.

{ Floating point

  Use the `-l` flag (`bc -l`) or the `scale` special variable:

code {
$ bc -q
100/1420000*44200
scale=4
100/1420000*44200
scale=5
3.09400
code }

}
{ Using bc in a one-liner for calculations

  With a → Linux/shell/bash/redirection#bash-here-string[here string], it is possible to calculate the result of an arithmetic expression in a one-liner:
code {
bc <<< "7.3 * 8.2"
code }

}

sa:

  → Linux/shell/commands[Shell commands] (such as `→ Linux/shell/commands/dc` and `→ Linux/shell/commands/expr`)
